                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 4.756,
                                "byte_start": 104794,
                                "byte_stop": 123916,
                                "text": "The second case -- the third case is not so complicated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 4.756,
                                "stop": 17.355,
                                "byte_start": 123916,
                                "byte_stop": 174280,
                                "text": "Here, a state court, that\u0027s Indiana v. Edwards, a state court found the criminal defendant in this case competent to stand trial if he was represented by counsel, mentally competent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.355,
                                "stop": 25.072,
                                "byte_start": 174280,
                                "byte_stop": 205104,
                                "text": "But he is not mentally competent to conduct the trial proceedings himself without a counsel, that\u2019s what the trial judge said."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.072,
                                "stop": 40.111,
                                "byte_start": 205104,
                                "byte_stop": 265290,
                                "text": "The Indiana State Supreme Court concluded that this Court\u0027s precedents don\u0027t allow that, that they require the trial court to allow the defendant, nonetheless, to conduct the trial proceedings himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.111,
                                "stop": 42.78,
                                "byte_start": 265290,
                                "byte_stop": 275948,
                                "text": "So, we have to decide whether that\u2019s so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.78,
                                "stop": 54.703,
                                "byte_start": 275948,
                                "byte_stop": 323700,
                                "text": "Does the constitution forbid a State from insisting that the defendant like this who the State thinks is not competent mentally to conduct the proceedings himself?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.703,
                                "stop": 61.726,
                                "byte_start": 323700,
                                "byte_stop": 351703,
                                "text": "Does it forbid a State for insisting that such a defendant proceed to trial with a lawyer, not without one?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.726,
                                "stop": 69.742,
                                "byte_start": 351703,
                                "byte_stop": 383782,
                                "text": "Thereby, denying the defendant the right to represent himself under the Sixth Amendment which we have explained the case called Faretta."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.742,
                                "stop": 80.525,
                                "byte_start": 383782,
                                "byte_stop": 426936,
                                "text": "We conclude that the State may insist a defendant be represented by counsel where that defendant is not mentally competent to conduct the trial proceedings himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.525,
                                "stop": 85.594,
                                "byte_start": 426936,
                                "byte_stop": 447207,
                                "text": "First, in our view, the relevant precedents do not decide the question presented here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.594,
                                "stop": 89.357,
                                "byte_start": 447207,
                                "byte_stop": 462254,
                                "text": "They assume the constitutional right of self representation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.357,
                                "stop": 95.091,
                                "byte_start": 462254,
                                "byte_stop": 485241,
                                "text": "They assume that that right set forth in Faretta can be limited in various ways."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.091,
                                "stop": 113.866,
                                "byte_start": 485241,
                                "byte_stop": 560265,
                                "text": "Second, the mental competency that a defendant needs to represent himself during the trial, can differ dramatically from the mental competency he needs to proceed to trial with a lawyer, and third, to permit a defendant to represent himself a trial when he is mentally incompetent to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.866,
                                "stop": 128.916,
                                "byte_start": 560265,
                                "byte_stop": 620556,
                                "text": "In our opinion, does not at all affirmed that defendant\u0027s dignity but rather it threatens to undermine the most basic of the constitution\u0027s criminal law objectives, namely, providing a fair trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.916,
                                "stop": 135.455,
                                "byte_start": 620556,
                                "byte_stop": 646678,
                                "text": "We add that the trial judge is in the best position to determine the presence or degree of the defendant\u2019s mental competence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.455,
                                "stop": 152.273,
                                "byte_start": 646678,
                                "byte_stop": 713970,
                                "text": "And we conclude that the State may insist that a criminal defendant be represented by counsel at the trial when that defendant who is mentally competent to stand trial with a lawyer, is not mentally competent to stand trial without one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.273,
                                "stop": 163.426,
                                "byte_start": 713970,
                                "byte_stop": 758587,
                                "text": "And these points which are a little abstract, are very concretely and very well-represented by the facts of this case right before us which are explained in the opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.426,
                                "stop": 168.836,
                                "byte_start": 758587,
                                "byte_stop": 780216,
                                "text": "So, we vacate the decision of the Indiana Supreme Court and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.836,
                                "stop": 174.576,
                                "byte_start": 780216,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion which Justice Thomas has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
